FC Minaj have signed former Reid FC and Nigeria striker Ugochukwu Oduenyi on a three-year contract in an undisclosed fee. The Ukrainian Premier League outfit unveiled the 24-year old striker on Thursday after both teams agreed on a personal deal. He has been handed over jersey #9 to relaunch his career. Oduenyi, who was a free agent after leaving Reid FC of Austria last year, will be hoping to reignite his career after turning down numbers of low profile clubs. The lanky striker started out at Festac-Lagos and a move to Ukraine could be a turning point to his career in a couple of years. “Ugochukwu, is a top-quality striker, his very happy to sign with FC Minaj and be part of the family of the club, he’s going to give 100% of is best and commit himself to the club, he loves scoring goals, I am very sure, he we take the club to another level in the premiere league,” Agent Salutan Momoh Danessi, who broke the news, said.